Square Inc. has hired former  Google
Inc. (GOOG)  executive Francoise Brougher as the companyâ€™s business
lead, overseeing areas including customer support, partnerships
and international expansion.  Brougher previously served as a vice president of sales and
operations at Google, focused on small and medium-sized
businesses, San Francisco-based Square said today in an e-mailed
statement. Before that, she was vice president of business
strategy at Charles Schwab & Co.  Founded by Twitter Inc. Chairman and co-founder Jack Dorsey, Square introduced a stamp-size credit-card reader in
2009 that can be used with smartphones and tablets.  Juniper Research estimates that the market for mobile
payments for physical goods may top $170 billion in transactions
